<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Well</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, he thought to himself, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>no use sitting around thinking about it.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> After readjusting his gunbelt so that his remaining gun was near his right hand, George headed down the tracks, hoping his leg would hold.<br>
<br>
After what seemed like days, but was in reality only 15 minutes, George paused and looked at his watch. Thinking that another platform couldn't be far away, George decided to continue heading in the direction he was. Two more steps is all he completed however, before he found himself in a web. His gun arm was too far up to grab the gun and his broken leg was at an odd angle. One thought coursed through Georges brain. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Weres.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dhampirlordofmallorea>Dhampir Lord of Mallorea</A> at: 7/2/03 5:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dhampirlordofmallorea>Dhampir Lord of Mallorea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#8B4513>(7/7/03 5:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In need of help, not wanting</span><hr size=1> George did not know how much time had passed. Hours. Days. Seconds. He just hung there, physically and mentally exhausted. Gradually his weight started to move forward. It was so gradual that George hardly believed that it was happening at first and thought his mind was playing tricks on him. But, as the one weak link, most likely an piece a rodent had some how managed to get to, finally gave way, there was no doubt left in George’s mind that he was being lowered to the ground.<br>
<br>
It took an eternity for the rest of the web to give way, but eventually, George was left lying on the ground. Mustering up the little strength he had left, the slayer of all that is not human headed toward a destination that he had not yet envisioned.<br>
<br>
George had managed to stand up against the wall and limp along like that. Suddenly, he came to what seemed like lights, brighter than any he had seen in a long time. So focused was he on this bright phenomena that he nearly missed seeing the two guards posted at the entrance to this haven of light. Stepping quickly, or as quickly as a man with a broken leg could, back into the shadows, George decided to listen in for a little while before finding away to sneak past. At least that’s what he told himself. In truth, he had to wait to gather his strength again.<br>
<br>
“A ghoul in the city. Can you believe it? A GHOUL. I tell you Vania’s lost her marbles.”<br>
<br>
Vania, that name struck a cord in George’s mind. That was the name of the human who saved that… <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>That ghoul you should have killed when you had the chance</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the voice in his head reminded him. Today George did not have the energy to argue. If he was going in this city, as the guard had unwittingly revealed to him, he would have to do it soon.<br>
